The devices to monitor people are increasingly demanded by parents who wish to monitor their children.
The fear for their child brings more people to think about the monitor through a GPS.
The system, introduced early to seek the cars can also be used to trace the movement of people and help for some cases such as that of the small exmple Anicka Janatkova.
The instrument is currently as large as a box of matches but will soon be the size of a shows.
The case of the small Anicka has moved a large number of people and they have begun to seek ways to better protect their children.
Even if the price is to disturb their privacy.
"We are trying to say to all people that this is not spying but just another way to reduce the likelihood that there is another tragedy," said Petr Pilin society MAcro Weil which is one of the suppliers of tracking devices on the Czech market.
"I admit that there may be cases of misuse of such devices, such as putting in the bag of a person who is not aware, but I have not yet met such cases".
"The majority of people are really customers who buy the product for security reasons, adds Pilin.
He said children should always know what purpose is used "the box" and how to use it in an emergency.
The child psychologist, Dana Bockova, drew attention if the child does not want to wear on him something of this type, it débarassera.
"And even the smallest may show a great creativity when it comes to express get rid of something when they do not want to be under control".
"The phones, which can be cut as these devices tracing, parents have already led to long delays," says Bockova.
In it, the fact that this type of device could help in the case of aggression is highly questionable.
"If it's a kidnapping prepared, the author will do everything to ensure that the child had no electronic device that can locate him".
"Currently, it is the phone".
"As soon as will develop the tracing, they (criminals) are the seek the because of the sale will be supported by an advertising campaign".
"In such cases criminals will always be ahead of the police," said the psychologist.
She admits that such devices can help during an assault not prepared by a paedophile.
According to Robert Cech of society RC Monitoring, which proposes tracing service both for cars for people, says that to have this type of device can help, even if it was destroyed in the case of an assault.
"The device can be parameterized such that it is in regular issue after a fixed period".
"In the event that the aircraft is destroyed, it's still the last position of the person concerned".
"The more expensive devices also have a point tiltmeter immediately the position of the person who has slipped and is found by lying down without moving," said Cech.
He said the so-called smart phones equipped with a navigation system, can offer a similar service after formatted with a special prologiciel.
The problem of current systems for tracking is that it is either a device similar to the ones they wear in Necklet, the size of a box of matches is the smaller phone devices.
You can always lose.
According to Pilina of society Macro WEIL, which is why the tests are being conducted to make devices that resemble common digital watches.
"This will have the advantage that the potential aggressor will not recognize the tracing system".
"Or it will account after a certain time, which would have given the police a little more time," he adds.
That the tracing system is developed in the form of bracelet necklet or utilisiera, it always the same technology as charting cars.
It is a combination of systems acquisition of a position via GPS (which is commonly used in autonavigation) and a mobile phone service that will alert the current position of a vehicle.
