"I can say that the award has encouraged not only my also my collaborators and increased our self-confidence to combat the competition", said today the winner of the competition last year.
At the beginning of the history of the company Farmet there was a desire to do something useful.
And so when the state has proposed to the father of Karel Zdrasky to rent the small workshop as compensation after the confiscation of their property by the Communists, it has not hesitated long, refused a career in a firm where he worked at the time, and created a society with a few comrades in the entourage of his father in the manufacture of plastic tubs.
Not very long after they began to specialize in the presses for vegetable oil.
After eighteen years it became the largest manufacturer of automatic presses in central Europe.
The company has been known even in the non-specialized audience after the success obtained in the competition through the media.
"Not only our customers have started to really better brand awareness Farmet but also foreign partners that have begun to realise that they were collaborating with a company that has received the most success in his country of origin," said Karel Zdarsky.
But the past year e not has not risen to Farmet only established the euphoria of victory.
The valuation of the company had been made from the economic performance of 2008 and part of 2009.
And precisely in 2009 and it was the most difficult year for the sale of engineering.
At the height of the crisis, which has not really affected citizens, companies were forced to halt their investment projects and begin to limit their achâts new materials and technologies.
"We have not escaped, of course, this situation".
"The turnover fell by 40 per cent, and we had to limit our production and even dismiss," said Karel Zdarsky.
A sustainable society must know that from time to time we must take unpopular measures.
But they have managed the situation correctly and have retained recipients results even if they were lower than they had before the crisis.
However, they have continued without compromise to invest in research and development.
"We have built with endowments a training and research centre, have strengthened the presentation of the society in salons-expositions and won the main awards in national exhibitions," said Zdarsky.
Everything suggests that the crisis is behind them.
The figures of affires back and with them the number of employees.
"The new winner I hope this nice feeling of victory but in a calm," said Karel Zdarsky.
The investigation, which removes senseless regulations.
The investigation into the Absurdité of the year is for the fourth time a part of the business clan.
Some absurd regulations have been removed.
The little glorieux winner this year of the survey on the Absurdité of the year was the obligation to make in the offices of documents that officials can get online.
More than one-third of the 4,000 voters voted for this.
For example, the administrations of Social Affairs paper asked an extract of the commercial register while the employee can get in two clicks of a mouse.
Things change thanks to the investigation.
"The administration of the Czech Social Insurance will ask more the extract from the register of trade for controls of insurance payments," said Jana Buranova, spokesman for the Czech Administration of social insurance (CSSZ).
Highlighting all regulations and decrees that companies and entrepreneurs must meet in the Czech Republic and eliminate those that are absurd is the meaning of this competition the Absurdité of the year.
This investigation is again this year for the fourth time part of business clan organized by Hospodarske noviny Hospodarske and has even greater popularity.
If the last year 3,000 voting occurred, it is at least 4,000 this year who have made their voices.
Not surprisingly, it is the most diverse countries in our legal obligations that do that curb the company, and that, this.
"We may be the number of paperwork for the tax returns for the top places in the world," said Karel Havlicek of the Association of small and medium-sized businesses and entrepreneurs in the Czech Republic.
The simplification of entrepreneurial activity becomes a declared goal of all governments in recent years.
In comparison with the world the situation in the Czech Republic does not improve at all.
According to the World Bank, the Czech Republic is to the 74 th place regarding the conditions for the company, or 8 places more compared to last year.
The support of the Absurdité of the year has been put in place for the first time in 2006, and continues each year by the same scenario.
Anyone can do state each year of administrative and bureaucratic nonsense from April to late September deadline before the close of the competition.
To reflect this ya the website www.firmaroku.cz. Next, the organizer of the competition chooses seven candidates for the "antiprix" and leaves the public vote during the month of October on the site www.firmaroku.cz / absurdita and www.ihned.cz.
The Absurdité that received the largest number of votes is declared the winner.
Until the last survey last year, it is a hundred or more exactly 105 regulations and décrêts who have lost their meaning of existence.
The remarks are sent by entrepreneurs but also professional unions and teachers.
Among the "finalists" of the competition, thus among the nominees is by example the requirement that the maintenance vehicles highways and expressways pay tolls, or that the contractors with 20 employees, repeignent two offices and two toilets every two years.
The list of seven proposals is published on the website of the competition.
The proclamation of the competition, which begins in early November on Wenceslas Square in Prague, is part of a regular happening involving figures from political and public life.
This year, for example, Eva Svobodova, director of the Association for small and medium-sized enterprises of Czech Republic or well Petr Kuzel, president of the Chamber of Commerce of Czech Republic, attended at the height of the competition.
'Economic prosperity cannot function when the state puts âtons in the legs of entrepreneurs and for that my goal is to remove, each year, at least three dozen paragraphs that today only complicate the business, "said Martin Kocourek, the Minister of Industry and Trade.
The effort to remove absurd décrêts is not an empty gesture.
In 2007, which was not welcomed people was the obligation of contractors to declare three days before the office to individual enterprise to the location of the company, the intention of going to an exhibition or a pilgrimage with a booth.
This requirement was removed with the ammendement of the Act on the individual.
The second requirement the most popular in 2007, which was to declare to the Office of the work a service for a foreign employee in 30 days, was removed with the text of the Act on the so-called green card.
And everything is ok until the third session of the competition.
The Absurdité of the year 2009 was the Order to physiotherapists to have a large mirror in their offices, a refrigerator and two automatic weigh-scales.
This has been changed by order of the Ministry of Health the year dernière-l' obligation to have a refrigerator has been removed.
