Two aircraft L-159 are for the first time in foreign hands in Spain.
Two aircraft L-159 of five in all, against which the Ministry of Defence has exchanged transport aircraft Casa C-295M, took off Tuesday for Seville in Spain where the manufacturer of aircraft Casa-EADS.
It is the first time that such devices become the property of someone other than the Czech army.
They have been abroad during exercises or demonstration flights.
It is two-seaters versions of which were until now in service in the Czech army and were flying.
Lestrois remaining aircraft are single-seater aircraft versions of L-159.
They stand at the moment and intermediate in Aéro Vodochody commercial Omnipol - the firm - the took into account last week.
According to Jan Pejsek of the press department of the Ministry of Defence, the departure of physical Vodochody aircraft is currently unknown.
'The L-159 single-seater aircraft planned for the exchange were taken on had stored for a long time without cause or cause additional investments for the Ministry of Defence ".
"The Q1 L-159 T1 were exchanged in the state," said for Pravo Pejsek.
He said that the army will not two-seater without because the department signed in May 2009 with Aéro Vodochody an agreement worth $200 million kroner for the transformation of four single-seater L-159 two-seaters unused in two.
The army has taken delivery of the first aircraft in July, the second scheduled for delivery by the end of this year.
According to Pejsek EADS is committed to introduce the aircraft in equipment to a number of NATO countries.
"In the contract it is clear that takes into account the aircraft L-159 is EADS and that they will be used to training pilots of NATO countries".
"It is therefore the case that takes into account how to achieve that," said Pejsek.
Hospodarske noviny announced some time ago that the Spanish army is not interested in the L-159.
The exchange of five L-159 for aircraft Casa and the purchase of three other planes to 3.5 billion kr was endorsed last year by the government of Mirek Topomanek.
The Ministry of Defence has not launched bidding and contacted directly EADS.
The management of Defense having a dispute while the exchange is a future export of L-159 abroad.
The Czech army bought Aéro Vodochody 72 apparatus and uses that 24, wanting to sell the rest.
The purchase of aircraft Casa will probably have legal implications.
The European Commission has filed a complaint against the Czech Ministry of Defence to the European Court of Justice because the aircraft should have been selected in a bid to the European level and never by directly contacting the manufacturer.
The army has already taken delivery of three aircraft Casa, the latter should arrive in Prague airport Kbely in two weeks.
An index that the index rim-fire is a sign of low risk cancer
Men who have the longer than the index rim-fire are exposed to a lower risk of having prostate cancer.
That is the surprising conclusion of a study published Wednesday by the British journal Cancer.
This may depend on the level of the male hormone testosterone.
"Our findings suggest that the length of the finger is a simple test of risk of prostate cancer, including for men before 60 years," proclaimed the co-author of the study Ros Eeles, professor at the Institute for Research on the cancer at the University of Warwick.
The finger could help to determine what men should undergo testing for prostate cancer, including by combining with the genetic risk or other aggrâvants factors such as family health antécedents, added Eeles.
During the period of 1994-2009 she followed with his colleagues in Britain more than 1,500 patients with prostate cancer and at the same time nearly three thousand healthy men.
More than half of the study participants had the index of the right hand shorter than the ring.
For them as for the 19 percent of those who had the fingers of the same length, it was found the same likelihood of prostate cancer.
In the case of those who had the index that the longer rim-fire the risk is, however, dropped to 33 per cent for men before 60 years the reduction of risk has risen to 87 percent.
The report by length of two fingers cited - trained during the prenatal period - shows including different levels of sex hormones facing the child in the womb.
Unless an index more testosterone is longer.
Previous research had shown that it is precisely the testosterone, which is helping to develop prostate cancer.
The pprofesseur Vacla, Erstaunen Paces Czech geneticist and former president of the Academy of Sciences, said to KTC that he is aware of this study but that he did not think, supposedly, that the relationship between the length of the fingers and the cancer was "completely demonstrated".
