The Americans have a new "weapon intelligent"
The U.S. military sent in Afghnistan a new weapon "smart", known only by the codename XM-25.
The generals believe that this new automatic rifle will influence the conflict there with the Taliban and "will change the game" to their benefit.
The new weapon is like a cannon super
The projectiles are guided by with a laser accuracy to within a few metres.
The special calibre ammunition 25-mm developed for the rifle and containing an explosive highly breaking, works in fact as small grenades.
You can program the ammunition so that they will soar in contact with the target but also at any point in their ballistic trajectory.
So you can use it against an enemy who hides behind a barrier, a wall or a ditch.
It is not protected from above and when it comes to top a deadly rain steel, that can disable also.
According to Richard Audette who took part in the development of the XM-25, the new rifle is the first infantry weapons that uses "smart" technology.
"The soldier is used mainly in such a way that he found the target, sends a laser that determines the distance, gives a specific aim point that it corrects his referred site and pulls the trigger.
"Let's say you have referred to 543 metres".
"When you press the trigger, the weapon is responsible and draws to the distance of 543 metres plus or minus 1, 2, 3 metres, Audette.
400 Jobs delocalized
The Group Fujitsu relocate its subsidiary of Bad Homburg.
Next year in July, 400 staff will transfer to Astro Park their place of work that is currently in the office building of the Place Mareinbader in the region of Bad Homburg.
The Japanese group Fujitsu relocate its branch of Bad Homburg in Frankfurt.
As the giant said Wednesday the specializing in the manufacture and the maintenance of computers, next year in July, the workplace 400 men and women, located so far on the place Marienbader of the town of Bad Homburg, will be transferred to Astro Park, huge office complex located on the street Lyoner Straße du Quartier Niederrad of Frankfurt.
A Fujitsu spokesman explained that in the medium term, the group should consolidate 100 other jobs still scattered so far in the region.
The supply of rental was extremely attractive. in addition, the offices to open area of Astro Park are better suited to working mode of collaborators.
In Bad Homburg, Fujitsu was just tenant.
The general manager, Bernd Wagner, said: "Frankfurt-Niederrad presents us with a central location with a remarkable infrastructure".
He says that the connection to the airport is of great importance to a comprehensive business as Fujitsu.
The new move of a major company inside the region has sparked yesterday the joy of disappointment caused the winners and losers.
The head of Economic Affairs of the municipality of Frankfurt, Mr. Markus Frank (CDU), said that once again, a "global player" had been conquered.
It is an "extraordinary" profession of faith on location ".
Fujitsu is to the city and its'implantation is a major boost for Niederrad.
The Mayor of Bad Homburg, Mr. Michael Korwisi (the greens), regrets the decision of Fujitsu.
Management has very soon informed the Municipality of this intention.
"It goes without saying that we have offered our assistance to this business," said Mr. Korwisi.
However, friendly relations could not change the difficulties of the computer manufacturer with the owner of the building of the Place Marienbader.
In the end, the economic reasons have been decisive.
It is now prevent a place so exceptional remains vacant for long.
"I hope that the owner and Lessor of the building will be coopératif."
Ten years ago, the building of the Place de l'Hôtel de Ville, used so far by the company Fujitsu and the "small vertical" neighbour, as well as the rest of the buildings on Place Marienbad, were part of the controversial construction project of the spa.
Result of a joint project of the municipality and a developer of private projects, a new entrance to the city was established between the station and the Town Hall, which drew widespread criticism, not only because of the impressive'aménagement surfaces that were formerly part of parking, but also because of the height of buildings.
In 2001, the company rating and investment advice, Feri, the manufacturer of computers for the travel distribution systems, Start Amadeus, and Fujitsu, manufacturer of computers at the time still associated with Siemens, moved into the buildings.
In 2006, The German group of specialized Frankfurt Immobilien-Chancen repurchased the buildings occupied by Fujitsu in the same time as the property fund Morgan Stanley. a year later, these buildings were sold to Spanish society Falcon Real Estate Investments SA, based in Madrid.
The group Fujitsu headquartered in Tokyo sees itself as the third largest provider of IT products in the world.
For example, it puts computers and servers available to businesses and also provides the essential service.
Its branch established in the Rhine-Main region of is one of the most important in Germany: Fujitsu is certainly far more employees in Munich.
The branch, Fujitsu Technology Solutions, leaves Bad Homburg to settle at Frankfurt-Niederrad. other subsidiaries present in this site are Fujitsu Services, and a company called TDS.
For this, 7,000 square metres have hired in the property Astro Park.
This complex of 20 years old, whose name recalls his plan in the form of star, houses, among other things, the headquarters of the Confederation of Industry électronique and electrotechnology.
