Excavation work Mysterious
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) provides new insights into a nuclear program developed by Syria.
But this is a country refuses to take a position on this topic, still less to submit to inspections of the agency.
On the night of 5 to 6 September 2007 around midnight, at least four Israeli I F-15 fighter aircraft attacked a mysterious cube-shaped building on Syrian territory.
It is located on the shore of the euphrate, the largest city near lies 30 miles: this is Dair.
His name appears in the IAEA documents, because it is a question of the reactor that Syria has reportedly built with the help of North Korea in stone parallelepiped, concealed in a valley marked by the absence of electrical current.
