More than 7.5 million voters were presented on 27 November, 70% of those eligible to elect mayors and councillors in five urban districts, in what is seen as a general assessment of the president, Ma Ying-jeou.
Mr. Ma has himself become a substitute for the feelings from the continent, with innovative business ties, including a partial free trade pact with the biggest reorganisation of relations with China itself since 1949.
Mr. Ma passed the test, but only just.
Although his party Kuomintang (KMT) has won three of the five mairies, he has failed to win a majority of votes.
