Xindu, an urban district of 680,000 people in Chengdu, has chosen to make a big operation of image.
Since 2003, the District has completed its street police in urban areas of 13 women, specially chosen for their appearance, their curve and their young age.
The idea is to give the police roughed a softer side, more female.
Unfortunately, even Scarlett Johansson could have difficulties to attract the look on this Brigade urbaine Souterraine China
And for good reason, critics say.
Unlike the police, these agents are allowed to enforce the municipal ordinances by imposing fines or other administrative sanctions.
But the Chinese news media portray a different reality.
