Zapatero and the German Red Line
Berlin has opted to remain in the euro, but he sets the terms for the whole of the Union.
Market tensions have led to a doble Government response.
On the one hand, José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero announced new adjustment methods, ranging from tax cuts for SMEs, regulation of private employment agencies or removal of 426 euros in aid to the unemployed without professional contributions to the privatization of 49% of Valencia, management of Barajas airport and El Prat and 30% of Loteries of the state.
For another, the Vice-President Elena Salgado, with the support of the former President Felipe González, is uniting to criticisms of Chancellor Angela Merkel in regard to its responsibility to detach the current crisis.
How do we interpret these movements?
It should be noted that the position of Merkel is not a mistake in its communication-based policy.
On the contrary, it is another limitation of the difficult process of redefining the euro.
And there, Germany has a radically new vision of what must be his future, which angered with that to maintain the old traditions of most of its partners.
In the face of resistance européennes, Germany are beginning to speculate on the possible three out of the crisis.
The first, a strong euro, integrated by itself, Austria and Holland, among other countries, and the south would abandon the currency zone.
The second, the recovery of Mark, although now it seems science fiction, with a current of opinion very favourable opinion, almost a 50% of the population.
The third, a new design of the euro, in line with the German proposals for greater macroeconomic control, budgetary rigour, fines on countries that transgress, the possible suspension of payments by one of them and extension to the private sector costs of potential adjustments.
The German position is clear and so long as it is defined, so now there is no place for an apology.
First, in 2009, when both IMF as the European Commission stimulated deficits, the German government has invented a constitutional reform to prevent them from 2016.
This was the first signal of divergence between what Germany would think we should do (plans of fiscal rigour and stability of public finances) and its European partners, ci-inclut France, practiced.
The second blow of the Central European countries was when Merkel has not extended the decision to rescue Greece.
At that moment, it was the subject of a ferocious criticism, but the truth is that the political consensus in Germany and public opinion and the published were against the rescue of Greece.
Finally, to the end of October, Merkel reiterates a clear position, calling for the reform of the EU treaties to make possible the rescue of a country and force at the same time the private lenders to bear a share of the cost.
This position has been interpreted as anti-European, because it has precipitated the Irish crisis and the rest.
But his proposal, although somewhat watered down, has been approved, and the following month, we should attend the process of reforme of the Union which is possible these measures from 2013.
Germany has drawn a red line that it did not believe cross-tabulate.
And she tells us all that, although now we must take measures with which it may not be too agree, from that date the former operation of the euro would have finished.
2013 Will mean the birth of a new currency zone, in which the countries that break the rules will be severely punished, they may be forced to be declared in default and, in this case, the private sector to bear as a party of costs.
Germany we said that we must follow a severe growth path with high rates of saving and investment, moderation in consumption, improvements in productivity and competitiveness and external balances positive.
An alternative based on debt and construction, with the huge holes in the balance of payments, such as the one who chaired the Spanish growth in the years of the boom, will simply not be tolerated.
The setting is clear.
And it would be wrong not to hear it.
It is not just extend the public deficit to 3 per cent in 2013.
What we demand is much harder.
And what it absolutely must not do in these circumstances is we deceive ourselves.
I hope that the current turbulence leave happen to us a tranquilité greater.
And that we can seize the opportunity that we were given, until spring 2013.
It appears that President Zapatero has also heard of this form and his dual statement (the promised reforms after the meeting of the past Saturday with large businesses and yesterday's announcement of the new measures) suggests that, despite criticism by Merkel, it opened the way to the thesis that we need to bring order to the house.
But the red line that Germany has drawn is, and they don't seem to move.
And among the possibilities being considered, you cannot exclude that to abandon a currency zone, packed with little countries too frivolous.
And in this case, Germany we can always say that it had warned.
Sport and law
The ruses similar to that of Alonso and Ramos against Ajax show ingenuity, but not the desire to escape punishment.
The expulsion ourdie in principle by two players of Real Madrid (Xabi Alonso and Sergio Ramos) during the match of 23 November against Ajax in the Champions League has spilled a lot of ink on the anti-sportif nature of such behaviour and if both players should be punished by UEFA.
As we know, a few minutes before closing the match (that their team was already clear), the two players have deliberately lost the time when they committed misconduct to determine the referee to show them the second yellow card.
As well, and given that Real Madrid will eventually be leader of his group, the two players serve the regulatory sanction during the game's next match against Auxerre dam and can pass without boxes to the next phase.
Finally, the Disciplinary Committee of UEFA has punished with two games the team coach, José Mourinho and various economic are the players involved.
The provocation of a yellow card in circumstances like this or similar is not a new practice, if not quite common in the world of football.
It is so widespread that it is part of the ethos of the rules non-écrites, but followed, the sport.
Part of the debate emerged in the case told is due to the fact that this has had as a team player as the entity of Real Madrid, which in its national anthem has the nobility and honour and in past occasions has fined its players for similar acts) and the orchestrated dramatization, apparently, by Mourinho, who adds one more episode in the history of histrionic technician dilated and provocative.
In any case, the debate asked whether this type of behaviour not expressly forbidden by the settlement contradicts the principles of sport, i.e., if with these actions it commits a fraud of law; because they are respectful shares with the sporting regulations, but seem to evade its meaning.
The issue is to consider the kind of damage they cause to the spirit of sport.
A property that includes sportsmanship is the physical integrity of the opposing players, an aspect that with these actions had not been put in danger, that is, there were no violent game.
Another of these assets referred with the game is correct that the team players benefit offenders unfairly of the team contrary, which is not the case either.
However, the paradoxical fact of the action of players of Real Madrid is that it does not countenance to what is normally characterised as cheating o fraud law because its violation of the rules has not been conducted in secret to try to avoid the penalty, but their action has specifically tried to be the most obvious possible to receive the penalization of the referee.
They expected and they gladly accepted the sanction.
Another issue is the kind of advantage that offenders get the willful misconduct examined.
Here it seems necessary to note that are not put at a disadvantage to rival and there has an advantage in the same match either, because obviously the result of the action involves letting their own team with fewer players.
And this is not a useful strategy for the next game not because the club could not count on these players.
The clear advantage lies in the fact that the players would begin the next phase of the Champions League without cardboards that can threaten their participation in a future match.
But this is a long-term benefit, with a degree of uncertainty, because the team could be eliminated suddenly and apart from that, with this action players perform a match penalty and spend the second cycle paperboards, in which the suspension due to the accumulation cardboards occurs with a less than in the first round.
So, climb the ladder, this is not so clear that this is an advantage.
Ultimately, these actions are not contrary to the spirit of sport, which is still the same party strategic decisions that support the benefit as much as the rules allow.
In our case, the players were not activated to avoid the application of the penalty (it would be a clear case of fraud the law), m otherwise they chose rather the moment in which they are subjected to it.
They have made a strategic decision without penalty or evade the escape this.
Even if the border between genius and the fraud law is diffuse, in this opportunity I think it was a clear case of genius.
The controversy, I believe, is because of two factors: because there were two auto-expulsions and because of the way to transmit the Director to the cause.
The damage caused to the principles of sport by these actions is not as much ethical as aesthetic.
