Thus, the 188 countries have received an indication to identify and locate Assange "for its provisional arrest and extradition."
Although Interpol cannot give the order to arrest a person affected by a red alert, many member countries, according to the explanation of the organization, consider the appeal red notice a clear pathway to the arrest - the National Police must achieve - especially if they have a bilateral extradition agreement, as is the case of Sweden and England, where it is thought that Assange is.
