In his first public appearance in the 16è Conference of the Parties to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change (COP16), Su Wei was assured that his country has made enormous efforts to reduce the trace of coal and convert his industry.
In fact, has exposé-t-il, the last four years his country invert has 245 million in efforts to reduce the emission of greenhouse gases.
Nevertheless, he made clear that China will not alter its objectives, but it will continue to work together with the international community in this area.
He said that the Chinese strategy in the field of climate change is divided into four areas: dialogue; construction capacity; construction of institutions and support for pilot programs.
There has been progress in all these areas, ci-inclut approval last year, a new Act of Energy, which recognizes the objectives outlined in regard to the reduction of greenhouse gases, has expliqué-t-il.
On the other hand, he pointed out that in China, federal authorities have worked in a coordinated manner with the local government and to achieve the objectives of energy savings, efficient energy use and reduce emissions.
In addition, a déclaré-t-il, there are various multiannual plans underway or completed, both funded by the Chinese government as by the governments of other countries.
For example, has mentionné-t-il, UNV of -Use Efficiente of'Énergie, which was implemented during the last five years and who has received investments of the United Nations (UN), the government and the private initiative.
There is also a draft provincial climate change, another for the change of filament lamps by efficient lamps and another for mitigation and adaptation, has détaillé-t-il.
At the same table, Martin Król, scientific adviser to the government of the country regarding climate change, provided that the efforts of China have been greatest of what it thinks.
For example, has exposé-t-il, the per capita emissions of greenhouse gases in China is three tonnes per person, while the United States is 100 tons; China is responsible for 9 per cent of the historic contribution in the contamination.
It made unprecedented efforts in the use of energy, how a 20% increase in energy efficiency in the last five years and plans to make a similar one by 2020, was déclaré-t-il.
