Romano the hunt for his first title
Rubén Omar Romano has had three defeats in finals he has had ups and downs in his career, but he has managed to achieve three times the decisive series.
With the duel of Santos Laguna and Monterrey in the final, plus two different styles which face, marked by their technicians, who find them a marked contrast with the results.
Rubén Omar Romano has had three defeats in finals, he had ups and downs in his career, but he has been able to achieve three times the decisive series, although to date it has not placed in the mile and that is why this opportunity is very special to him.
The Argentin eventually console with the medal of sous-champion, he remained a step behind the winners and curiously with the same team he played consecutive final.
The strategist santiste arrived at its first final as entraineur Opening the Tournament in 2002, when he took the reins of Morelia with which he lost with an overall score of 4-2 against Toluca; later, in the Closing 2003 it happened in decisive duel and lost again with the overall result of 3-1 and this was precisely against Rayados.
With Santos Laguna, already in the Bicentenary 2010 Tournament, again against the Diablos, Rubén has suffered a new setback, because his team has done an equal match 2-2 against the Choriceros after 210 minutes of play, but in a series of penalties he obtained an advantage to 3-1 with two opportunities to obtain the title and eventually three of his players have missed 11 metres and has suffered the jump at the result of 4-3.
Rubén lost two finals with the Diablos Rojos and one with Monterrey, his rival in the tournament, therefore it does not have the same fate, he tries to detach from the evil spell to celebrate a title for the first time, although he says that for him the institution is more important.
"I want to be champion, I don't want to break any statistics, it is for a club, not for a passion that I have, and therefore I get the title, but what I mentioned before is more important," said the helmsman when asked what would be its weak spots in the finals.
He remembers a lot of the last final, which he assured that he has learned a lot, "the only lesson that we can accept is that until the referee whistles is the final, we cannot celebrate, we are prepared in line, players, too, for the last time, with two penalties to draw we were already prepared to run and I think this is a lesson, before the end of the match cannot be fêter."
He knows that the series could be defined by penalties, which do not worry, as he says in its players: "it never tries to arrive at a series of penalties, we are trying to finish in the scheduled time, but sometimes we have that we prepare, the previous tournament we were prepared, unfortunately the destiny we made a wrong turn, sometimes it is the emotions or anxiety to take the title in our hands, hands it has eluded us, it has served as a lesson for that final and we hope that we have more in those circumstances".
Romano now has the opportunity to not be a technician sous-champion and taste for the first time the glory offered by the securities.
The European Union is changing the rules for the visa
People should go to the centers of Service to the Visa callers before their interview in the Consular Section; the cost the waiting time would be diminished.
On 10 January 2011 processing visas at the embassy and consulates of the United States will change.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants will have to submit the centers of Service for the Visa callers (CSA, according to its Acronyms in English) before their interview in the Consular Section.
The staff of CSA will take the biometric information from the applicant, which will be revised by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will present some advantages for candidates, including the following:
The total cost to treat the visa will be lower, it will be no need to make a payment to get an appointment, another payment for the treatment of visa and another for the mail service delivers the document.
The aspiring will make a one-time payment to cover the three services.
The current rate will remain the same: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 in the case of visas with application (ci-inclut visas for temporary workers) and $390 for the visas of traders and investors.
People who want to renew their visas will not attend an interview with the Consular Representative, they will only to the CSA closer to where they submit documents and we will take their fingerprints.
Due to the fact that biometric information will be taken in the CSA, applicants wishing to a second appointment to be interviewed in the Consular Section remain there for less time than before.
Similarly, visa applicants to Consulates Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer pay the extra service fee of $26.
For more information on the new procedure to apply for the visa, visit the following page http: / / mexico.usembassy.gov / boletines / sp101201 _ Visas-FAQs.html
NASA will announce the Discovery of extraterrestrial
The U.S. space agency has cited the press to make a discovery that tomorrow will be the impact on the search for living in space.
The National Administration Aeronautics and Space (NASA) of the United States will tomorrow, Thursday, a discovery astrobiologique, which could prove the theory of the existence of extraterrestrial life.
The discovery will be made in a press conference tomorrow, Thursday, at 1: 00 p.m. at NASA headquarters in Washington for experts in astrobiology, the science that studies the origin, evolution, distribution and future of life in the universe.
When she quoted the press, NASA has ensured that it would have to be the impact on the search for extraterrestrial life ", which has aroused speculation by experts from other countries.
The discovery could prove the theory that there are creatures similar to us and in hostile ambient thought uninhabited and put on the table the possibility of becoming intelligent beings as humans if their living conditions are improved.
It seems that there is talk of a microbe found at the bottom of the Mono Lake in the Yosemite National Park, California, who lives in a ambiant thought too venomous for any form of life, because the lake is rich in arsenic.
In any form, the creature uses the arsenic as a way of life and this ability makes us think that a similar life could exist on other planets that have not our atmosphere.
According to the astrobiologistes, if these agencies use the arsenic in their metabolism, this proves that "there is another form of life, a second form of life, different to that as we know it."
The space agency will the true scope of the discoveries in the press conference tomorrow, Thursday.
At the conference will be the géobiologie Pamela Conrad, who is studying the possibility of life on Mars; and the biologist Steven Benner, one of the scientists who study Titan (the largest satellite Saturn), under the prospect that his chemistry is similar to that of Earth.
