14 Alleged drug traffickers arrested
A dozen searches were carried out in Estrie, Wednesday, in the context of the dismantling of a network of production and sale of cannabis.
Fourteen people were arrested and will face various charges.
The searches were conducted in Sherbrooke, Orford and Stoke, mostly in places that would have been used in the production of drugs.
"Approximately 750 cannabis plants, four kilos of hashish, money and equipment used for the production were seized," said Louis-Philippe Ruel, spokesman for the Surete du Quebec.
In all, eleven men and three women have been arrested, including the two alleged leaders of the network, two men of Sherbrooke.
Those arrested were to appear in court in Sherbrooke in the hours following their arrest.
They could face charges of production of cannabis, possession for the purpose of trafficking, conspiracy and theft of services, among others.
These searches took place following a lengthy investigation, which lasted almost a year.
"This is information received from the public that allowed us to make the arrests," said Mr. Ruel.
Some 70 officers from regional investigation module Estrie of the Surete du Quebec police Service Sherbrooke and the RAMQ of Memphrémagog, police took part in the police operation.
