The Government of Quebec has been asked to commit themselves financially in the redemption of the cinema complex eXcentris by the Angus and the Parallèle Society, agreed to work together, but up to a loan only.
The Angus Development Corporation and the Parallèle, who hoped a donation of seven million of the Ministry of Culture to buy at Daniel Langlois the film eXcentris on Boulevard St. Lawrence in giving full cinéphilique vocation, do not get what they wanted.
The government agrees to get involved in the case, but on its own terms.
Rather than the gift expected, the Quebec government proposes a loan with the amount would be below expectations Initials, which could be a viable solution to favourable conditions, at least in the opinion springs from pharmacies of the state.
A first action plan and a request from 12.8 million had already been rejected by Quebec last spring, but requests have since been revised downwards.
A proposal and an action plan has been sent to the Minister St-Pierre by the President of the Society of Business Development culturelles (SODEC), François Macerola, who leads the file of eXcentris.
He sent a final report about 10 days ago.
But the cabinet Counter-proposal reached the SODEC Tuesday.
The Parallèle and Angus have until 31 December to respond.
However, it appears that the idea of donating the State should really be dismissed.
