A source close to the investigation, the investigations focus particularly on the eligibility and functioning of La Ciotat, which collects the waste of Aubagne as well as some cities of the urban community of Marseille (MPM).
Clotilde Reiss case: the Élysée Palace has exaggerated the mediation of Syria
For more than 10 months from July 2009 to May 2010, the fate of Clotilde Reiss, the young French researcher arrested in Iran for "'espionnage", held the opinion in breath in France, put diplomacy on alert, diplomacy and accentuated the deterioration of relations between Paris and Tehran.
All under the gaze of US diplomats.
The American documents obtained by WikiLeaks and consulted by Le Monde reveal some below of this crisis.
They describe how the Elysée explained its strategy to the Americans, up to give advice for the treatment of their own crises "hostages" in Iran (a small group of hikers).
They show how French officials have sought to convince Washington that the release of the young French woman had not resulted in return for the release of Majid Kakavand, an Iranian detained in France and wanted by the United States justice for trafficking materials to the benefit of the Iranian nuclear programme.
Finally, they place under a harsh spotlight how the French Presidency has sought to manipulate the media to give credence to the idea that the Syrian President Bashar Al-Assad, had played a central role in the release of Clotilde Reiss.
In fact, there was nothing.
A diplomatic cable written on August 12, 2009 in Paris is entitled "Iran: French comments on how to manage cases of hostages".
The Elysée adviser for the strategic affairs, François Richier, accompanied by the director of the Quai d'Orsay for North Africa and the Middle East, Patrice Paoli, met with the American diplomat Kathleen Allegrone.
They explain the French Method.
They advise Americans to do the same to repatriate their nationals forcibly held in Iran.
"Make noise," they say, "martelez" in the media the words "basic human rights", "innocence", "immediate release".
It is necessary in order to embarrass the Iranian regime, sensitive to its image.
"Do it all the more as Iranians are asking you not to do."
